HEADWORD: Inharmoniousness
<hw>In`har*mo"ni*ous*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality of being
inharmonious; lack of harmony; discord.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>inharmoniousness</qex> of a verse.</q> <rj><qau>A.
Tucker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inharmony</ent>⟦br⟧
